==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caryophyllidae
<hw>Caryophyllidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a group of families of mostly
flowers having basal or free-central placentation and trinucleate pollen
(binucleate pollen is commoner in flowering plants); it contains 14
families including: <fam>Caryophyllaceae</fam> (carnations and pinks);
<fam>Aizoaceae</fam>; <fam>Amaranthaceae</fam>; <fam>Batidaceae</fam>;
<fam>Chenopodiaceae</fam>; <fam>Cactaceae</fam> (order
<ord>Opuntiales</ord>); <fam>Nyctaginaceae</fam>;
<fam>Phytolaccaceae</fam>; it corresponds approximately to order
<ord>Caryophyllales</ord>; it is sometimes classified as a
superorder.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> subclass Caryophyllidae.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caryophyllin</ent>⟦br⟧
